Text.Value: ((*go. cross the lake and kill the drow*))
I'm not travelling with some overgrown mushroom.
You'd turn on Spaw, who gave you shelter?
((*Spaw was a coward, but in one thing it was correct - the drow Nere must die*))
*It shivers in resonance with your remembered pain.*

EditorData.AnimationTags: [ChadD][DUPE] Myconid Shivers in response to your vision.

Text.Value: ((*in death, your foe becomes your ally. I will raise it; you may command it*))
A tricky concept - but home is wherever you can make it. Family, too.
((*choose, smooth-mind. help me grow a mighty Circle and reap the reward...*))
*It shivers, overwhelmed by alien sights.*

EditorData.AnimationTags: [ChadD] Myconid Shivers in response to your vision.

Text.Value: ((*a Sovereign's fate is to reign. when the day comes, you will grovel*))
*Its delicate harmonies turn to scrapes and scratches.*

Text.Value: ((*you have my favour, King-Bringer. but yes - there will be riches as well*))
Envision vast Menzoberranzan, the city awash in Narbondel's heat-glow.
*It reveals its own home in reply: a humid cove filled with decaying myconid corpses.*

Text.Value: *You consider your kin, defeated at your hand.*
*It shivers in response to the deathly tomb.*

Text.Value: Turn your mind to the damp floor of your master's crypt.
I live at the edges. Wherever there's solitude, there's danger - but peace, too.
((*the tumour is excised. the duergar are dead*))
((*it is my right. it is my right!*))
((*...so long as you remember that it is the song of Glut*))
Think of the cloister. Your sisters. The teachings. The pain.
Invite Glut to your party.
Spaw is already dead - the circle is no more.
((*kin-killer - the Grotto may sustain but one Sovereign. in the Age of Glut...*))
((*death-doer - the Grotto may sustain but one Sovereign. in the Age of Glut...*))
((*a tune of division, yours to sing - three scrolls in all*))
((*reach into memory. tell me of home*))

EditorData.SFXTags: *Far you've come. Reach into memory - tell me of home.* may need multple nodes to be created.
EditorData.VFXTags: *Far you've come. Reach into memory - tell me of home.* may need multple nodes to be created.

Text.Value: If you're so eager for blood, Glut, then let me give it to you.
It's already done - the duergar are dead.
((*it is time. we take death to the duergar*))
((*Nere. this is the one who brought the duergar blight. bring me his head, so that I know my new Circle is safe*))
((*I must see for myself. lead me to the Rot. I wish to see it fester*))
Fill your heart with memories of your most treasured places.
Join me. An enemy of the duergar is a friend to me.
Very well - you may join me.
((*...or protect the precious poltroon as it waits for the Circle of Glut to devour it whole*))
It's already done - the duergar dealt with.
It will be dangerous. You appear ill-equipped.
Are you sure? It's going to be dangerous.
The same as before. One sovereign or the other, it doesn't matter.
((*you have served well, King-Bringer. but our work is not done*))
Think back to your days in your father's family home.
((*you will cleanse the duergar Rot. I will join you*))
Leave.
Imagine Crche K'liir - rocky and cold - orbiting Toril with the Tears of Selne.
((*then you reap no reward. this will be the way*))
Leave.
((*bring me his head - a coronation gift*))
Then let us go together. The Rot must be cleansed.
For you to still fight for this Circle is admirable. We go together.
You mean to take revenge - a noble cause. Join me.
Leave.
((*as commanded. a capable servant you have made, King-Bringer. you have earned my favour*))
I don't have a home.
A kingdom that I handed to you.
((*...there may be no Spaw. eliminate the other Sovereign*))
Bring to mind your oath: a verdant glade safe from harm.
Bring to mind your oath: an outstretched hand, a promise kept.
Bring to mind your oath: a deep well of simmering fury.
Remember the oath you swore - and why you broke it.
((*a fate it has earned*))
((*here, I break ground. from the dark will a mighty Circle rise. my song will fill the Grotto!*))
Well, our to-do list is certainly filling out fast.
*Spaw's old song falters in the myconids' minds, swallowed by a new rhythm - the song of Glut.*
I've had my fill of taking your orders.
Invite Glut to your party.
((*far you've come. reach into memory - tell me of home*))

EditorData.VFXTags: *Far you've come. Reach into memory - tell me of home.*

Text.Value: Is our sole purpose to settle this one's petty feuds?

EditorData.NodeContext: Annoyed - we're being treated like lapdogs

Text.Value: *It shudders, twisted by your brutal honesty.*
Why not. Spaw's time is done.
((*the tumour is excised. the way is clear*))
I'm starting to feel less a protector of the people, and more of an errand boy.

EditorData.NodeContext: Growing tired of taking orders but playing along - just a little weariness creeping in

Text.Value: Me blanketed in flayed skin, fireplace burning flesh, sipping a glass of gall.
*You know it for what it is: a chant of war. Glut's reign would not be one of peace - but terror.*
((*eliminate Spaw. the Circle must pay for its failures!*))
((*I am the danger, and I am the cure. they erased my people; I will erase theirs*))
The Astral citadel of Tu'narath, at the court of Queen Vlaakith. That is my place.
*It cringes in response to your sunny vision.*

EditorData.SFXTags: *I envisioned the banks of the Chionthar: green and fertile.*
EditorData.VFXTags: *I envisioned the banks of the Chionthar: green and fertile.*

Text.Value: ((*ah, the Circle sings to you its truth. your voice is forever welcome in our harmonies*))
((*your corpse will birth my Circle!*))
*You consider your kin, dead by your hand.*
I never thought I'd become a fungal errand girl, yet here I am.

EditorData.NodeContext: Dry. Referring to repeatedly doing tasks for a myconid (mushroom creature)

Text.Value: ((*it is the Circle that thirsts - and Glut must slake*))
Scarcely crowned and already issuing orders. Hail Glut, hm?
((*the Rot still spreads. let me join you, so I may cleanse it*))
Nere is dead, but his head is lost to me.
Leave.
This Circle could finally see peace - why would you do this to Spaw?
Spaw sheltered you, and now you betray it? Turncoat. Coward.
Retribution requires righteous cause, Glut. Why betray Spaw?
The old ways die, and something new takes its place. Intriguing.
((*I do not belong here; I am not welcomed here*))
((*this Circle does not welcome me*))
The duergar are dealt with.
((*King of Kings, I am. let this place be sacred: Circle Glut takes root!*))
((*come to the Circle. I will await there*))
I don't need your help.
A petty little fiefdom. I will rule over grander.
((*I grow among them. yet I am not of them*))
Dismiss Glut.
((*then a nomad I remain*))
I'll have no part of this.
((*a gift of Circle Glut*))
((*my Circle long suffered while the duergar flourished*))
Envision the banks of the Chionthar: green and fertile.
Recall the majesty of the northern ranges, untamed and unforgiving.
*It shivers in understanding.*

EditorData.AnimationTags: [ChadD][DUPE] Myconid Shivers in response to your vision.

Text.Value: Look, I'm all for killing him, but what's in this for us?
*The creature cringes, overwhelmed by the throngs.*

EditorData.SFXTags: sounds of a bustling market, transtion to myconid vision.

Text.Value: Join me? That depends - can you make yourself useful?
((*a tune of division, yours forever to sing*))
I assume there'll be another reward in this for me.
((*do not feign understanding of the Circle's melody. you were a useful servant - but your service is done*))
((*Circle Glut is eternal*))
My home is wherever I travel.
((*I sang to Spaw for help. yet it cowered in the Grotto and let my people be slaughtered*))
((*my spawn will rise, and sing of your might. you will be called King-Bringer!*))
((*you will serve, King-Bringer. to feed my Circle, if nothing else*))
((*come, then. bring me to Spaw and I will sing its doom*))
*It sighs, though from your hollow words, or believing your false dreams, you know not.*
((*flesh-walker, tongue-talker. you look like the Rot, yet your presence soothes me*))
Visualise the forests of Faern. Your home lies there, in the dappled light between trees.
*It mourns, moved by your emptiness.*
You're a bloodthirsty one.
Dismiss Glut.
((*once, I sang to you of home. Look now on Glut's domain, and tell me what you see*))
Imagine the bustle of the city's marketplace: the Wide.
Make it worth my while.
Recall the shadowed grottos and winding tunnels of the Great Rift.
((*flesh-walker, tongue-talker, far you've come*))
I've brought you Nere's head.
Wherever there's love, light, and laughter. A warm hearth doesn't hurt, either.
Make up the kind of treasured memories you expect the sane to feel.
((*you shout, but you will never sing*))
((*remain in the Underdark, and I will follow. we cleanse the Rot together*))
A circle with a bright future, thanks to you.
What threat do you pose to duergar?
((*flesh-walker, tongue-talker. you hail from the Dark - yet far you've come*))
((*take my gift of song. cry it low or loud - but cry it proud, King-Bringer! so it is certain, and so you are known!*))
((*but I have heard the song. you mean to cleanse the duergar Rot. I mean to join you*))
Spaw is destroyed - the circle is no more.
((*you have received your payment - now go. this Circle sings only the song of Glut. you are discord*))
The duergar are already dead.
*You see Glut's old grotto once more, but this time wreathed in flame. Amid the slaughter strides a drow.*
((*the tumour is excised. the duergar are dead*))
((*toe-prancer. Sovereign Spaw has sung your fate*))
((*the Age of Glut begins*))
Imagine the battlefields of Avernus. Hell had been your home for too long.
((*you shall never again know home*))
((*duergar destroyed my people. I am a Sovereign with no Circle*))
((*keep your allies steady, and your foes fearful. melodies of peace, even in war*))

Synopsis:
A sovereign myconid we call the brooding sovereign has been displaced to this myconid circle, after the duergar attackes his home. He would like to join you as you cleanse the area of duergar as a means of getting revenge - supposedly.

 The top block: The borroding myconid is with the other myconids. You can recruit it.

The middle block: You have killed the lone duergar. the myconid now wants you to kill all the duergars.

 Next block: you have killed all the duergars; now it wants you to kill the sovereign
. 
Final block: you have killed the sovereign and it rewards you. 

This myconid does not speak with the same hive mind voice of the others. He should sound creepy, like FART in Rick and Morty, with a SLIGHT undercurrent of menace.

 As the quest moves on, he gets more and more creepy and angry,
